fields.title: Auckland CBD
fields.description: A bustling metropolis and the economic heart of New Zealand, Auckland CBD offers stunning waterfront views, a vibrant nightlife, and world-class dining.

fields.title: Wellington
fields.description: The capital city of New Zealand, Wellington is known for its cultural scene, government institutions, and picturesque harbor, surrounded by rolling green hills.

fields.title: Christchurch
fields.description: Known as the Garden City, Christchurch is a blend of English heritage, innovative urban design, and beautiful parks, recovering dynamically after the 2011 earthquake.

fields.title: Queenstown
fields.description: A paradise for adventure lovers, Queenstown is famous for its stunning lake and mountain landscapes, world-class skiing, and adrenaline-pumping activities.

fields.title: Dunedin
fields.description: A charming city with Scottish heritage, Dunedin is home to historic architecture, wildlife attractions, and a thriving student community from Otago University.

fields.title: Rotorua
fields.description: Renowned for its geothermal activity and Maori culture, Rotorua offers steaming geysers, bubbling mud pools, and rich traditions.

fields.title: Hamilton
fields.description: Located along the Waikato River, Hamilton boasts beautiful gardens, a growing caf√© culture, and a vibrant nightlife.

fields.title: Tauranga
fields.description: A coastal city with stunning beaches and a warm climate, Tauranga is a popular spot for relaxation, surfing, and exploring Mount Maunganui.

fields.title: Napier
fields.description: Famous for its Art Deco architecture, Napier is a charming city with vineyards, beautiful coastal views, and a rich history.

fields.title: Nelson
fields.description: A sunny city on the South Island, Nelson is known for its vibrant arts scene, craft breweries, and access to Abel Tasman National Park.
